    "answer": "The current state of gasless transaction infrastructure on Status Network is highly advanced, with the network operating a fully gasless Layer 2 built on the Linea zkEVM stack, which eliminates transaction fees entirely and funds itself through yield from bridged assets and native app revenues ([Result 2](https://our.status.im/status-network-in-2025-building-a-gasless-and-private-layer-2), [Result 4](https://our.status.im/status-network-first-gasless-l2)). Status has developed a native gasless execution model that does not rely on relayers or subsidized payments, utilizing cryptographic mechanisms like RLN (Rate Limiting Nullifier) to prevent spam without traditional gas fees ([Result 6](https://docs.status.network/general-info/gasless-transactions)). This infrastructure supports seamless, free interactions for users and applications, with ongoing development and testnet deployment.\n\nIn comparison, approaches based on EIP-4337 (ERC-4337) for account abstraction focus on enabling smart contract wallets with customizable validation and payment logic, including optional paymasters that can sponsor gas fees. ERC-4337 operates entirely on smart contracts and introduces UserOperations that are bundled and processed by relayers, allowing for flexible transaction validation, batching, and fee sponsorship without changing the core Ethereum protocol ([Result 3](https://our.status.im/what-is-account-abstraction), [Result 7](https://coinstats.app/news/91339ca9fe0bb797ce501ea15e0b32211eb0d720f526bc918e8305071ce7ec60_What-Is-Account-Abstraction-ERC4337-and-Gasless-UX)). Recent developments have seen ERC-4337 become operational on mainnet, with ongoing enhancements such as native support for passkeys and improved user experience, but it still relies on relayers and mempool mechanisms for transaction processing.\n\nOverall, Status Network's gasless infrastructure is a native, protocol-level solution that eliminates fees through innovative economic models and cryptographic spam prevention, whereas EIP-4337 approaches are more about flexible, programmable account management and fee sponsorship via smart contract wallets and relayers. Both aim to improve user experience and reduce transaction costs, but Status's current implementation is more deeply integrated at the protocol level for gasless transactions ([Results 2, 6, 10](https://our.status.im/status-network-in-2025-building-a-gasless-and-private-layer-2), [https://status.network/docs/gasless-transactions](https://docs.status.network/general-info/gasless-transactions)).",
